edu.first.identifiers

Interface PositionalActuator

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Output

    public interface PositionalActuator
extends Output
    The general contract for classes that actuate to a position. Uses a number as the setpoint position.

    May 22 13

    • Method Detail

      • setPosition

        void setPosition(double position)
        Sets the actuator to a position. There should be no delay between the time this method is called and when the actuator starts going there, but it is possible that the finishing of this method does not mean that it has achieved the position. That case should be well documented and explained.
        Parameters:
        position - new position to set the actuator to
